	<section id="recipe">
		<p>
			Children love nutella. Adults love nutella. The French
			eat it with their crÃªpes; the kids with everything. So
			why not you?  
			Oh right, because it's unhealthy, and since you've come
			to <span class="nm">Lila, Chop!</span> for recipes, then you certainly care
			about that!  
			Well, how about protein-nutella
			served clean, healthy, and deliciously nutritious?
		</p>
		<table class="ingredients">
			<caption>Ingredients</caption>
			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th class="amount" colspan="2">amount</th>
					<th class="name">name</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="1"></td>
				<td class="unit">scoop</td>
				<td class="name">
					<a href="http://www.amazon.com/dp/B000GIQSV6/?tag=lich048-20" class="amazon">Fitnessguru's One Whey Mint Chocolate</a>
					<span class="altor">or</span>
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="alt amount" data-lilachop-amount="1"></td>
				<td class="alt unit">scoop</td>
				<td class="alt name">
					any chocolate-flavoured protein powder
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="1"></td>
				<td class="unit">cup</td>
				<td class="name">Alpro hazelnut milk</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="0.5"></td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td class="name">frozen banana</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="2"></td>
				<td class="unit">tbsp</td>
				<td class="name">
					<a href="http://www.amazon.com/dp/B005P0I322/?tag=lich048-20" class="amazon">Bob's Red Mill hazelnut meal</a>
					<span class="altor">or</span>
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="alt amount" data-lilachop-amount="2"></td>
				<td class="alt unit">tbsp</td>
				<td class="alt name">finely ground hazelnuts</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="1"></td>
				<td class="unit">tbsp</td>
				<td class="name">raw cacao powder</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="0.5"></td>
				<td class="unit">tbsp</td>
				<td class="name">cacao nibs</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="1"></td>
				<td class="unit">tbsp</td>
				<td class="name">chopped hazelnuts</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="alt amount" data-lilachop-amount="1"></td>
				<td class="alt unit">handfull</td>
				<td class="alt name">ice (optional)</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="alt amount" data-lilachop-amount= "3"></td>
				<td class="alt unit">drops</td>
				<td class="alt name">
					<a href="http://www.amazon.com/dp/B00282UD0K/?tag=lich048-20" class="amazon">liquid Stevia, hazelnut</a> 
					(optional, for sweetness)
				</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
		<div class="servings">
			Servings: 
			<input id="servings" type="number" min="0" step="1" value="1" onchange="changeservings(this.value);" />
			(Total Calories: <span data-lilachop-amount="330"></span>.)
		</div>
		<p>
			This was one of my first original recipes, so it has a
			sweet (pun intended) spot for me.  
			I learned that the trick to making healthy treats out
			of traditionally unhealthy recipes, such as nutella, is
			to substitute sugar for Stevia, flavouring with
			flavoured whey protein powder, cream with frozen
			banana, and whole-milk with plant-based milk.	
		</p>
		<table id="steps">
			<caption>Steps</caption>
			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th class="amount" colspan="2">time</th>
					<th>instruction</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount"></td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td>
					Put aside the raw cacao powder, cacao
					nibs and chopped hazelnuts for
					garnishing last.
				</td> 
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount"></td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td> 
					Blend all other ingredients together in a
					high-speed blender until smooth and
					creamy.
				</td> 
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount"></td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td>
					Pour smoothie into a tall glass and garnish with raw
					cacao powder, cacao nibs and chopped
					hazelnuts.  
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount">10</td>
				<td class="unit">min</td>
				<td>
					Serve cold, and enjoy!
				</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
		<p>
			To make the recipe leaner, simply use less hazelnuts,
			and replace the frozen banana with crushed ice.
			Remember, the creamier the consistency and the more
			frozen the smoothie is, the more it will taste like ice
			cream. 	
		</p>
